messages.title: Strong, Stable Leadership In The National Interest
messages.content: Jeremy Quin is standing with Theresa May. Together, they provide the leadership the United Kingdom needs to make the most of Brexit and deliver a strong economy.

keyPolicies.policyDescription: Making Brexit a success is central to our National Interest. We need to ensure strong and stable leadership to handle Brexit negotiations with a clear plan to benefit Britain.

issues.brexitEurope: Making Brexit a success is central to our national interest.
issues.economy: The Conservatives promise a strong economy with job security and rising living standards. They aim to provide real opportunity and support for all, making sure the economy works for every household.
issues.health: Healthcare priorities include supporting the NHS to ensure it is a good place for getting old, having children, and receiving emergency care.

leaflet.personalStatement: Jeremy Quin supports Theresa May in delivering for Britain and is committed to working hard for his constituents.

images.caption: Jeremy Quin with Theresa May, showing their partnership and shared vision.

leaflet.additionalNotes: The leaflet emphasizes the contrast between 'strong, stable leadership' with Theresa May and 'a coalition of chaos' with Jeremy Corbyn.
